# AyurGlow Product Catalog & Category Filter System

## Background

Currently AyurGlow has only 4 products in a flat array with basic categories (`MOISTURIZE`, `CORRECT`, `CLEANSE`, `HAIR CARE`). The products page has no filter UI. We need to expand the product catalog with dummy products and implement a robust category/filter system inspired by **Foxtale** (collection tabs) and **Dr. Sheth's** (skin type filters), adapted to AyurGlow's Ayurvedic brand identity.

## Research Summary

### Foxtale.in Collection Tabs
- **Product Type Tabs**: Serums, Cleansers, Moisturizers, Sunscreens, Masks, Toners, Bodycare
- **Filter axes**: Skin Type, Skin Concern, Ingredients
- **Presentation**: Horizontal scrollable tab pills at top of collection page

### Dr. Sheth's Filters (hdt-filters)
- **Skin Type**: Dry, Oily, Normal, Sensitive, Combination
- **Concern**: Pigmentation, Acne, Dryness, Blackheads, Ageing, Uneven Skin Tone, Brightening, Dark Spots
- **Ingredient**: Vitamin C, Hyaluronic Acid, Kojic Acid, Niacinamide
- **Routine**: Cleanse, Treat, Moisturize, Protect

### AyurGlow Adaptation (Ayurvedic Focus)
Merged modern skincare classification with Ayurvedic dosha-based philosophy.

